@page "/privacy"
@page "/privacy-policy"
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]
@layout PublicDocumentLayout
@rendermode InteractiveServer

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy - PTDoc</PageTitle>

<article class="public-policy-page" aria-labelledby="privacy-title">
    <header class="public-policy-page__hero">
        <p class="public-policy-page__eyebrow">Privacy Policy</p>
        <h1 id="privacy-title">PTDoc Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>
            This policy describes how PTDoc supports secure patient intake, communication, and
            physical therapy documentation workflows for participating clinics.
        </p>
    </header>

    <section class="public-policy-page__section" aria-labelledby="privacy-data-title">
        <h2 id="privacy-data-title">Information We Process</h2>
        <p>
            PTDoc may process patient contact details, appointment information, intake responses,
            insurance and authorization details, care-team information, documentation data, and
            communication preferences when a clinic uses PTDoc to support patient care.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="public-policy-page__section" aria-labelledby="privacy-use-title">
        <h2 id="privacy-use-title">How Information Is Used</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>To verify patient identity for secure intake access.</li>
            <li>To help clinics collect and review patient intake responses.</li>
            <li>To support appointment, documentation, billing, and care coordination workflows.</li>
            <li>To send transactional email or SMS messages requested by the clinic or patient workflow.</li>
            <li>To maintain security, auditability, and operational reliability.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            PTDoc does not sell patient information and does not use intake SMS consent for marketing
            messages.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="public-policy-page__section" aria-labelledby="privacy-security-title">
        <h2 id="privacy-security-title">Security and Healthcare Privacy</h2>
        <p>
            PTDoc is designed for HIPAA-conscious healthcare workflows. Access to clinical and patient
            information is controlled through authentication, role-based authorization, audit trails,
            and secure communication patterns. Clinics remain responsible for their own privacy notices,
            patient authorizations, and healthcare compliance obligations.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="public-policy-page__section" aria-labelledby="privacy-communications-title">
        <h2 id="privacy-communications-title">Email and SMS Communications</h2>
        <p>
            PTDoc may send transactional messages such as intake links, one-time access codes,
            appointment-related reminders, and care-related follow-up. SMS recipients can reply
            <strong>STOP</strong> to opt out or <strong>HELP</strong> for help.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="public-policy-page__section" aria-labelledby="privacy-contact-title">
        <h2 id="privacy-contact-title">Contact</h2>
        <p>
            Patients should contact their clinic for questions about their medical record or care.
            For PTDoc platform privacy questions, contact
            <a href="mailto:ccc@blackhousedevelopers.com">ccc@blackhousedevelopers.com</a>.
        </p>
        <p>Effective date: July 6, 2026.</p>
    </section>
</article>
